ğŸ“˜ Overview

Tourist Itinerary Planner is a smart web-based project that helps tourists plan their trip efficiently by selecting, scheduling, and mapping the best places to visit based on their available time and preferences.

It uses three powerful algorithms â€” Knapsack, Activity Selection, and Hamiltonian Path â€” to optimize the itinerary for:

Best possible enjoyment (ratings)

Time efficiency (no overlaps)

Logical travel route (each place visited once)

This project can be applied to any city or travel destination, not just one specific location.

